			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Okay reading through this I agree on some items and disagree on others......
<br />

<br />
In some ways it helps mages for semi-hassel free play time. I didnt start playing a mage till after T-rods were nerfed, and honestly I would have hated to just be a summong bish and not enjoy the game's content as much.
<br />

<br />
The main reason they nerfed T-rods in the first place was an unbalance. Mages used to summon a crapload on raids and people would pick them up off the ground and keep clicking them. So yes reuse timer helped that unbalance.... then the issue becomes if casters really want them non-lore that bad, possibly petition to make them non-lore/no-drop?
<br />

<br />
On the flip side of that arguement though I feel it's unneccessary to lore tag the gear or even the solid inviso stones. Just like pet classs bug us for multiple sets of pet gear, why should they not be able to bug us for items like that? It poofs anyhow, and either way they can't wear more than one shoulder slot at a time, etc... and if by chance you actually need to wear it then you go through the pain of destroying or giving yours to the person that requests it and then making another, or not being able to summon a bag full and save time cause your wearing a peice. 
<br />

<br />
And really if soe was worried that much about players corpsing extra sets then they should worry about the pet gear too. People do it all the time.
<br />

<br />
As far as the lore tag on the inviso stones go, yes I could see it might create a problem, but if soe is worried about unbalance of it, put a level restriction on them (ex: make restriction same level and above as those who can stable invis themselves).
<br />

<br />
Unlike any other player buffs with the exception to a select few spells, what we do not only requires summoning, but hitting trade witch can get time consuming if there not on your cusrsor (if thats the case you had to remem half your spells which also takes time)
<br />

<br />
Long story short... lore can seem to be a pain sometimes, but I can also see non-lore becoming an issue to. I love playing my mage, and honestly I'd hate to have to put aside the conent more than the time I do already do to be someone's bish.  
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
.....end rant</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
